00:01:04.209 --> 00:01:07.250
So what is LiveOps?

00:01:07.250 --> 00:01:10.360
I think many of you have already
heard of this definition,

00:01:10.360 --> 00:01:13.500
but LiveOps is running
games as a service.

00:01:13.500 --> 00:01:15.520
The characteristics
of the smartphone

00:01:15.520 --> 00:01:17.770
as an always connected
device actually

00:01:17.770 --> 00:01:20.320
allow the game developers
to frequently interact

00:01:20.320 --> 00:01:23.560
with the end users by
providing additional content

00:01:23.560 --> 00:01:26.320
and information as a service,
which does not necessarily

00:01:26.320 --> 00:01:29.200
involve traditional APK updates.

00:01:29.200 --> 00:01:32.410
So when these services are
provided in the right way,

00:01:32.410 --> 00:01:34.560
it actually drives
user engagement,

00:01:34.560 --> 00:01:37.270
stimulates monetization,
and even reduces

00:01:37.270 --> 00:01:40.180
player turn, which has a
significant impact on the life

00:01:40.180 --> 00:01:42.660
cycle of your game.

00:01:42.660 --> 00:01:45.330
So what happens when
the service is not

00:01:45.330 --> 00:01:47.380
enough for your end users?

00:01:47.380 --> 00:01:51.810
So this is the typical
revenue trend curve

00:01:51.810 --> 00:01:55.990
that games that deliver content
only via traditional APK

00:01:55.990 --> 00:01:59.190
updates, but not via LiveOps.

00:01:59.190 --> 00:02:02.910
For each update, you see
some spikes in revenue,

00:02:02.910 --> 00:02:06.180
but it slows down pretty fast,
and you cannot maintain active

00:02:06.180 --> 00:02:09.360
users by the next update, and
the spike size gets smaller

00:02:09.360 --> 00:02:11.350
and smaller each time.

00:02:11.350 --> 00:02:13.950
We call this a shark
fin [INAUDIBLE] problem,

00:02:13.950 --> 00:02:16.410
and obviously this is
not ideal if you want

00:02:16.410 --> 00:02:20.040
to make your game sustainable.

00:02:20.040 --> 00:02:24.460
So in what way does
LiveOps solve this problem?

00:02:24.460 --> 00:02:27.550
So LiveOps is basically
a strategic distribution

00:02:27.550 --> 00:02:30.880
of frequent content updates
in between traditional APK

00:02:30.880 --> 00:02:32.220
updates.

00:02:32.220 --> 00:02:35.730
These are basically categorized
into two things, the sales

00:02:35.730 --> 00:02:39.580
and events, and both of them
often contain a new content

00:02:39.580 --> 00:02:41.700
into your game economy.

00:02:41.700 --> 00:02:46.600
And typically these are provided
in a limited time basis, which

00:02:46.600 --> 00:02:51.100
is a key for you to motivate
your users to participate

00:02:51.100 --> 00:02:54.430
actively in the activity that
is happening inside our game.

00:02:54.430 --> 00:02:58.780
When these sales and events
are provided in the right way,

00:02:58.780 --> 00:03:02.055
LiveOps can drive a consistent
heartbeat of revenue

00:03:02.055 --> 00:03:04.690
and engagement,
and which helps you

00:03:04.690 --> 00:03:09.210
to avoid shark fin [INAUDIBLE]
problem for your game.

00:03:09.210 --> 00:03:10.850
So that is LiveOps.

00:03:10.850 --> 00:03:13.750
And from here I like to touch
