00:03:13.750 --> 00:03:16.430
difference between Japan
and Western Europe,

00:03:16.430 --> 00:03:19.250
what's unique about Japan
in the context of LiveOps.

00:03:21.800 --> 00:03:26.330
So first of all, Japan is a
really LiveOps heavy market,

00:03:26.330 --> 00:03:29.360
compare of the Western
regions, and its daily revenue

00:03:29.360 --> 00:03:32.550
fluctuates a lot due to the
high frequency of LiveOps.

00:03:35.210 --> 00:03:37.790
One of the reasons behind
this is the popularity

00:03:37.790 --> 00:03:39.480
of the gacha model.

00:03:39.480 --> 00:03:41.930
The gacha is the
in-game lottery system

00:03:41.930 --> 00:03:46.290
which is widely adapted to the
top grossing Japanese games

00:03:46.290 --> 00:03:48.890
as the core
monetization mechanics.

00:03:48.890 --> 00:03:52.640
Because gacha is a really good
fit with our limited time sales

00:03:52.640 --> 00:03:55.700
and events, Japanese
developers run

00:03:55.700 --> 00:04:00.874
a lot of these as a driver for
their revenue and monetization.

00:04:00.874 --> 00:04:03.540
Of course, they are also running
a lot of other types of events,

00:04:03.540 --> 00:04:06.500
like in-game login bonus
and the in-game quests,

00:04:06.500 --> 00:04:09.230
but the gacha is something we
cannot ignore as an important

00:04:09.230 --> 00:04:12.390
part of Japanese
LiveOps culture.

00:04:12.390 --> 00:04:14.670
And another reason for
the huge fluctuation

00:04:14.670 --> 00:04:17.070
of daily revenue in
Japan is the first day

00:04:17.070 --> 00:04:19.910
of the month by extradition.

00:04:19.910 --> 00:04:22.130
Japan is known as
a country where

00:04:22.130 --> 00:04:26.690
DCB is a really popular form of
payment among the mobile users.

00:04:26.690 --> 00:04:29.270
And as you know, DCB
has a monthly cap,

00:04:29.270 --> 00:04:31.550
so if you keep the cap in
the middle of the month,

00:04:31.550 --> 00:04:35.120
you have to wait until the
next first day of the month,

00:04:35.120 --> 00:04:38.030
because the cap gets
refreshed on that day.

00:04:38.030 --> 00:04:41.000
So knowing that timing,
Japanese developers

00:04:41.000 --> 00:04:43.880
always bring the most
powerful LiveOps event

00:04:43.880 --> 00:04:45.980
on the first day of the month.

00:04:45.980 --> 00:04:49.460
And the Japanese users also
know that is the best timing

00:04:49.460 --> 00:04:51.620
to use the money in the game.

00:04:51.620 --> 00:04:55.460
So the combination of this
developer strategy and user

00:04:55.460 --> 00:04:58.780
behavior actually comes
together and always causes

00:04:58.780 --> 00:05:02.300
the huge revenue spike on the
first day of the month for most

00:05:02.300 --> 00:05:06.200
of the games altogether, which
is pretty unique for the Japan

00:05:06.200 --> 00:05:07.040
market, I think.

